cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CE

The paper presents a machine learning approach to predict drug-drug interactions, which involves the use of artificial neural networks and graph similarity measures. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as the paper involves the use of computational techniques to predict drug interactions. The use of graph similarity measures also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the field of graph theory and algorithms (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of their approach in drug development and prescription, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of computational biology and bioinformatics (cs.CE).
